meaning: Godot tried to create another instance of NavigationServer, but another one exists.
causes: A module or plugin is trying to create another instance of NavigationServer.
The initialization code for NavigationServer is being executed twice while the engine is starting.
A module or plugin tries to re-register NavigationServer even though Godot already registered it.
fixes: Ensure that NavigationServer is registered only once.
Remove any calls in the modules or plugins you have installed which may try to create another instance of NavigationServer.
If modifying the engine source, check for any calls to re-execute the initialization code for NavigationServer.
notes: This error normally does not appear in standard GDScript/C# usage.
NavigationServer is managed by Godot, user code should not cause this error to happen.
